# 🏗️ System Design: Opportunity Management System (BQS)

## 1. Overview
This document outlines the architecture and workflow for the **BQS Opportunity Management System**, a multi-role platform designed to transform CRM data into strategic intelligence.

---

## 2. Business Objective Layer

The BQS platform is designed to transform "Gut-feeling" sales into "Data-driven" strategic decisions.

*   **Strategic Alignment**: Ensure 100% of pursued deals match organizational goals.
*   **Operational Excellence**: Reduce bid turnaround time by 30% through automated assignments.
*   **Financial Integrity**: Mandate strict margin thresholds (PAT Margin) before sign-off.
*   **Risk Mitigation**: Early detection of "Red Flags" via standardized scoring.

---

## 3. Role Mapping to Actual Org

| System Role | Actual Organizational Title | Primary Responsibility |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Geo Head (GH)** | Executive Leadership / BU Head | Strategic P&L Oversight |
| **Regional Head** | Territory Lead / Ops Manager | Regional Pipeline Velocity |
| **Sales Head (SH)** | Vertical Sales Director | Sales Strategy & Team Direction |
| **Practice Head (PH)** | Solutions Delivery Director | Capability & Resource Alignment|
| **Solution Architect (SA)**| Technical Pre-sales / SME | Solution Design & Scoring |
| **Legal/Finance** | Central Compliance Team | Risk & Margin Approval |

---

## 4. PostgreSQL Schema Design (Core Entities)

### 4.1 Core Opportunity State
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `opp_id` | `String (PK)` | Oracle CRM Opportunity ID |
| `workflow_status` | `String` | `NEW`, `GH_ASSIGNED`, `TECH_ASSESSMENT`, `SUBMITTED` |
| `assigned_sales_head_id` | `String (FK)` | SH responsible for strategy |
| `assigned_practice_head_ids`| `JSONB` | Multi-practice support |
| `assigned_sa_ids` | `JSONB` | SAs assigned for technical scoring |
| `pat_margin` | `Float` | Profit After Tax margin |

---

## 5. Workflow Diagram (Sequence)

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[1. CRM Sync] --> B[2. Geo Head Assigns SH/PH]
    B --> C[3. SH/PH Assigns SP/SA]
    C --> D[4. Technical & Commercial Scoring]
    D --> E[5. Compliance Review (Finance/Legal)]
    E --> F[6. Final Management Approval]
```

---

## 6. Frontend UX Layer

*   **Adaptive Navigation**: Sidebar items change based on the user's active role.
*   **Workflow Steppers**: Visual tracker for deal progress.
*   **Actionable Inboxes**: Dedicated "Tasks assigned to me" on the home page.
*   **Leadership Dashboard**: High-level metrics with drill-down capability.

---

## 7. Decision Intelligence Layer

*   **Win-Rate Analytics**: Correlation between BQS scores and final outcomes.
*   **Resource Bottlenecks**: Identifying overloaded practices or SAs.
*   **Automated Flagging**: Alerts for deals with <15% margin or >4 risk level.
*   **Regional Trends**: Benchmarking performance across different Geographies.

---

## 8. Implementation Notes

1.  **Concurrency**: Implement record locking when an SA is actively scoring.
2.  **Audit Logs**: Capture every assignment and status change with a timestamp.
3.  **Real-time**: Use WebSockets for immediate inbox updates on status changes.
